nodes.title: üëë HashText manual subject
widgets_values: # add your manual description for the subject after the hash # pretty 21 year old blonde European woman with curtain bangs hairstyle, dressed in red belted short dress

Preparation Steps:

1. Install MokkaBoss1 Node Suite and any others missing using the ComfyUI-Manager "Missing Nodes" feature

2. The seveninabox node requires personalisation of sampler settings. You need to ammend the "..ComfyUI_Mokkaboss1\model_settings\model_data.py" to fit with the models you use and ammend the settings you use. Then you will always have these default setting available as soon as you change the model.

3. Switch comfy to "Link Render Mode" hidden to hide all the noodles. This can be found under the settings (Gear Icon above Queue Prompt)

4. Include the Images needed to run the flow. I have provide example images
    A) Example Input for Image to Image (I2I_Input.png) found in the same folder as this workflow.
    B) Example Input for Background (I2I_Background.png) founf in the same folder as this workflow.
    C) If you want to use section 6 which generates a slideshow image for 1080p vertical monitors:
        C1) Black_Background.png
        C2) White_PhotoFrame.png
        C3) White_TextFrame.png

Running the Workflow:

The nodes are pinned to avoid unwanted moving around and disturbing the karma. The colour scheme is as follows. Nodes that provide a choice for the workflow flow are coloured yellow. Nodes that are meant to be opened and collapsed (revealing other nodes behind) are in purple. The rest of the nodes are in light blue.

There are some choices along the way

The scenario selector works as follows:
Choice 1) This is an image to image workflow based on the input image including subject and background
Choice 2) This is an image to image workflow based on the input image subject and a colour gradient background
Choice 3) This is an image to image workflow based on the input image subject but replacing the background with another image.
Choice 4) This is a text to image workflow based on an empty latent image.

Also there are various options to manipulate the text prompt aswell.
  
3. Choice 2A - This allows you to select the subject in the photo (wearing female clothes or male clothes)
4. Choice 2B - This allows you to select the custom background (indoor, outdoor or custom)

Last important point there is a node called "AspectRatioCondition" that checks if the image is 9:16 required for running section 6 of the workflow. If the image is not 9:16 the workflow will terminate  at this stage. This feature still allows auto queue. 

When you run the workflow, it will stop at the step "Preview Chooser". You need to highlight the image and press "Progress selected Image" or "Cancel current run". Alternatively you can of course just set this to "pass through" and then it won't stop each time. This is good if you are using the auto-queue feature.

hope you get some use from this workflow

MokkaBoss1
